cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the use of convolutional autoencoder networks for modeling sparse structures in 2D, 3D, and 4D space-time. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of unsupervised learning techniques for downstream tasks such as handwriting recognition, segmentation for parts in 3D objects, segmentation for objects in 3D scenes, and body-part segmentation for 4D wire-frame models generated from motion capture data, suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of convolutional autoencoder networks for modeling sparse structures suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of 4D space-time models suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
